ThinkPart(
    type='think',
    think='Now I have a comprehensive understanding. Let me compile my findings.
\n\n## Major Issues Found:\n\n### 1. Auth Controller Route Prefix Bug\n`apps/api
/src/modules/auth/auth.controller.ts` defines `@Controller("api/v1/auth")`, but 
`main.ts` already sets `app.setGlobalPrefix("api/v1")`. This means the actual ro
ute becomes `/api/v1/api/v1/auth` which is incorrect. It should be `@Controller(
"auth")`.\n\n### 2. Missing Validation Decorators on RegisterDto\n`apps/api/src/
modules/auth/dto/register.dto.ts` has no `class-validator` decorators (`@IsStrin
g`, `@IsNotEmpty`, etc.), so the global `ValidationPipe` with `forbidNonWhitelis
ted: true` and `whitelist: true` won\'t properly validate the DTO. The `birth_da
te` should probably also be validated as a valid date.\n\n### 3. Missing Module 
Documentation\n`docs/modules/INDEX.md` references three module docs that don\'t 
exist:\n- `admin.md`\n- `blocks-reports.md`\n- `content-moderation.md`\n\nThis w
ill cause `make check-docs` to fail because it checks for dead links in markdown
files.\n\n### 4. BDD Step Definitions are Skeletons\nMost BDD step definitions u
se `autoBindSteps(feature, [commonSteps])` but `common.js` likely only has gener
ic steps. Looking at the infrastructure BDD steps, they\'re just stubs. The actu
al test scenarios aren\'t properly implemented. However, this is somewhat expect
ed for infrastructure bootstrap.\n\nLet me check common.js to see what it contai
ns.',
    encrypted=None
)
